Today is Mother’s Day and I came into McDonald’s to buy Double cheeseburgers for 20 women that are confined to a rehab center due to Covid they have not been able to go outside and said that they would love a McDonald’s burger because they have not had McDonald’s in over three months these are all struggling mothers trying to get their life back on track when I ordered the burgers and asked the gentleman how long it would take and told him where I was taking the food the manager Was so kind and offered some fries to go with the burgers he told me To tell the ladies that McDonald’s cares  💝💝 This act of kindness really touched my heart I don’t know his name I’m sorry I didn’t ask for it before I left the store but I really appreciate the heartfelt gesture the ladies were so happy when they receive the food they were screaming through the phone thanking me since I couldn’t see them face-to-face only pass the food to the counselor through door It was so nice that during a time  like this when all the world is in crisis  that someone has a heart and the power to do something kind for another human being Thank you to the manager of the McDonald’s at 1275 Fulton Street in Brooklyn I hope the owner and the McDonald’s Corporation realizes that you are truly a credit to the company. May God bless you and your family I was really touched by your act of kindness on Mother’s Day 💕 Lisa Davis

This is not a rating of McDonalds in general, I love McDonalds.  This is a rating of this particular location which is the absolute worst I’ve been to. On three different occasions while staying in the area I went, assuming my last experience had to have been a one off. Nope. This place is terrible. Not only is the food somehow not good (dry stale burgers and salt less over cooked fries) but they take forever to make the meal cause they are too busy chatting with friends. Once they even wouldn’t take my order because they were too busy talking. I had to but in and ask to have my order taken. You can imagine the attitude I got. That McFlurry wasn’t even mixed when it was handed to me. Just some cookie crumbles on ice cream. I brought up the issue with McDonalds, and they did absolutely nothing. Go to Taco Bell across the street! Or there is a McDonalds just a 10 min walk down Fulton. Just stay away from this place.
